HEADWORD: Lauraceous
<hw>Lau*ra"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Laurus</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Belonging to, or
resembling, a natural order (<ord>Laurace⟦ae⟧</ord>) of trees and shrubs
having aromatic bark and foliage, and including the laurel, sassafras,
cinnamon tree, true camphor tree, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laurate</ent>⟦br⟧
